I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to formally announce my resignation from my position at National Grid, effective December 31, 2023. This decision was not made lightly and is the result of careful consideration of my career goals and personal aspirations.

It has been an incredible journey working at National Grid for the past six years, and I want to express my heartfelt gratitude for the opportunities I've been given during my time here. The experiences, challenges, and accomplishments have all contributed to my professional growth, and I have learned so much from the amazing people I've had the privilege to work alongside.

I am particularly grateful for the support and mentorship I've received from you and the entire team. Your guidance and encouragement have played a pivotal role in my development, and I will always carry these lessons with me in my future endeavors.

As I transition to the next phase of my career, I look back on my time at National Grid with fond memories. The relationships I've built and the knowledge I've gained will always hold a special place in my heart.

I am committed to ensuring a smooth handover of my responsibilities over the next few months to minimize any disruption to the team. Please let me know how I can assist in this process.

I would also like to take this opportunity to thank the entire National Grid family for their support and collaboration. I am confident that the company will continue to thrive and achieve great success in the future.

If there are any formalities or procedures I need to follow during this transition, please advise me, and I will make sure to fulfill all of my responsibilities.

Thank you once again for the incredible journey, and I wish National Grid continued success and prosperity.

Sincerely,
